## Part 7: Bug Discovery and Fix

**User:** Inventory numbers are still not correct. Numbers are repeating in Month on Month view. And they are not there in the Weekly view.

**Claude:** Investigating root cause.

*[Claude inspects the file structure:]*

```
Line 396: buildInvTable('w-inv', WP, INV.wWH, INV.wST);tml lang="en">
Line 397: <head>
Line 398: <meta charset="UTF-8">
```

**Root cause found:** A previous string replacement operation searched for `</script>\n</body>` to inject the INV data, but accidentally matched mid-line — splitting the `<html lang="en">` tag and embedding `tml lang="en">` directly into the JavaScript call. This caused the `buildInvTable('w-inv', ...)` call to be syntactically broken, so neither monthly nor weekly inventory rendered at all.

**Fix applied:**
```python
# Reconstruction approach:
# 1. lines[397:] = intact HTML from <head> onwards
# 2. Prepend correct <!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en">
# 3. Inject INV data cleanly before </script>

main_body = '\n'.join(lines[397:])
new_html = '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang="en">\n' + main_body
# Inject INV data block before closing </script>
new_html = new_html.replace('</script>\n</body>', INV_JS + '\n</script>\n</body>')
```

**Verification after fix:**
```
✅ Single <html> tag
✅ 13 distinct monthly values for VC Eye (1423458 → 1989934 → 1089942)
✅ 6 weekly values for VC Eye (1490453 → 1089942)
✅ buildInvTable called twice (m-inv and w-inv)
✅ No file corruption
```

*[Fixed dashboard presented — inventory working correctly in both Monthly and Weekly tabs]*

